description:
We’re growing and looking for a **Creative Strategist** to join our Marketing team. Join the team behind one of the world’s fastest-growing gaming marketplaces.

 **About** **Eldorado.gg**  

Launched in 2019, headquartered in Vilnius, Simbiocity (formerly Technopolis);  

A leading digital marketplace for in-game items, accounts, and services;  

Supporting 150+ popular games including GTA5, Roblox, FC25, RuneScape, World of Warcraft, League of Legends, Fortnite, and more;  

Trusted by gamers worldwide with over 7 million monthly visits;  

Built for security, speed, and simplicity in digital trading;  

A team of 100+ people focused on delivering an exceptional experience for our users.



**BREAKDOWN**

* Own the creative direction for paid marketing channels, ensuring messaging and formats are aligned with business objectives and performance targets;
* Translate performance data into actionable creative insights, strong campaign concepts, and testable hypotheses;
* Drive creative ideation for new campaigns, messaging angles, and content formats;
* Maintain a consistent brand voice across website and marketing content;
* Work with Product and UX teams to improve website content for clarity, trust, and conversion;
* Support A/B testing efforts by helping test and optimize content across key website journeys;
* Create clear customer-facing copy for purchase, delivery, and dispute flows.



**SKILLS YOU’LL NEED**

* Experience developing creative for paid acquisition channels such as Meta, TikTok, YouTube, Google, or similar platforms;
* Strong understanding of direct response marketing, conversion-focused messaging, and funnel-based thinking;
* Understanding of UX writing and how content supports clear, intuitive user journeys;
* Ability to write conversion-focused copy that drives action and improves customer understanding;
* Comfortable using data, A/B testing, and experimentation to improve content performance.

**WHAT WE OFFER**

* Hybrid work model: work 4 days at our Vilnius office (Simbiocity), and 1 remote.
* Office perks: free parking by the office, a fully stocked kitchen, Friday bun breakfasts, and a gaming room (table football, driving simulator, PS5, Xbox One). Pets are always welcome, and we love a good get-together - from game nights to sports events.
* Development: internal library, latest tools and technology, professional conferences, and mentorship to level up your skills, opportunities for internal career growth.
* Health and fitness: Private health insurance (after trial), join your colleagues for fun, no-cost volleyball games at Delfi Arena, sick days (no doctor’s note needed).
* Extras you’ll love: Monthly top-ups for your Eldorado.gg account (after trial), gifts for graduations, weddings and new parents, partner discounts, and referral bonuses.
**GROSS SALARY**  

The salary range for this position is €2500 – €4000 gross per month, depending on your experience.


Think you’re the right fit? Let’s create something epic together.

*If you’re looking to make the best co-op games in the world, you’ve come to the right place. We're proud to have some of the best game makers and collaborators in the industry working with us. What's more, we're a fun bunch of game developers, who love to indulge in our passion for video games together. Our games are not for everyone. Are they for you?*
**We are now looking for a Senior Tools Programmer** 
 As a senior tools programmer at Arrowhead, you will be part of our tech team while working closely with designers, artists and programmers to analyze and improve their workflow.




**What You'll Do**
* Maintain and iterate on existing tools and editor features, ensuring that overall quality and usability meet the needs of the project;
* Work together with all feature teams to design and develop new tools, increasing quality of life for all;
* Help to identify workflow issues and bottlenecks in our pipelines and continuously work to improve them;
* Cooperate with the Engine Programmers to implement features in the engine when needed for tools development;
* Communicate and follow up progress on tools with the content developers.


**Our requirements**
* 5 years of technical work experience in the video games industry;
* Experience working with C# / C++;
* Experience with script languages such as Lua, Javascript or Python;
* Experience writing game development tools that improve the user experience and workflow;
* Familiarity with an existing game engine with understanding of game engine and editor concepts;
* Strong debugging and problem solving skills;
* Demonstrates dedication to high quality standards;
* Good collaboration and communication skills with a cooperative attitude;
* Good English communication skills (verbal and written).


**Bonus qualifications**
* Experience working with WPF;
* Experience working with Chromium Embedded Framework;
* Experience working with TeamCity.
* Familiarity with DCC tools such as Maya, Blender, or Houdini.


****How to apply****
 If you think that this position matches your background and skills, we would love to hear from you. Please submit your CV in English as soon as possible. We ask that your application always include relevant work samples or a link to your portfolio.




 We interview candidates continuously and hire when we find a good fit.




**Practical Information**
**Scope:** 
 Full-time: 40 hours per week with initial 6 month probation period.




**Location:** 
 Office first, hybrid solution possible. You need to be eligble to work in Sweden.




**We are a pet friendly office! You can expect to find cute dogs and occasionally some cats around.**
**What we offer** 
 Arrowhead Game Studios is a growing team of about 140+ people, best known for our co-op titles. Despite our size, we remain a friendly and down to earth bunch, who love to indulge in our passion for video games together.




 Located in the heart of Södermalm, in Fatburen in the middle of the Game Dev scene we enjoy everything Stockholm has to offer. The is a a lot of different types of activities immediately available on our doorstep.




 Our talented developers are crucial to our success, therefore we put a lot of emphasis in creating and maintaining a prosperous culture. We’re committed to open and transparent communication. Your ideas are welcomed, valued, appreciated - the ceiling for creative discussions is high.




 We also have numerous work benefits for all our employees. You can read about them here!
